<exercise checkit-seed="0003" checkit-slug="P4" checkit-title="Random Variables">
  <statement>
      
      <p>
          A professor decides against using OER's in their statistics class and uses a publisher text instead.  The students have the option of purchase a hardcopy text for 150 dollars, access to a flash e-text for 95 dollars, of a bundle of both for 225 dollars.  Let <m>X</m> denote   the amount spent for this course by randomly selected a student in statistics.  Consider the following probability distribution table for <m>X</m>
      </p>
      
      <p>
          <me>
              \begin{array}
              \\
              \hline
              X_i 
              &amp; 150
              &amp; 95
              &amp; 225
              \\
              \hline
              P(X=X_i)
              &amp; 0.443
              &amp; 0.425
              &amp; {}?{}?{}?
              \\
              \hline
              \end{array}
          </me>
      </p>
      
      
      <p>
          <ol>
              <li>
                  What is the value of the missing entry?
              </li>
              <li>
                  Find the expectation of <m>X</m>, <m>E(X)</m>,  and interpret what it means in context of this problem.
              </li>
              <li>
                  Find variance of <m>X</m>: <m>Var(X)</m>.
              </li>
              <li>
                  Find the standard deviation of <m>X</m>: <m>\sigma_X</m>.
              </li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
         <ol>
             <li>
                 <m>P(225)=0.132</m>.
             </li>
             <li>
                 <m>E(X)=136.525</m>.
             </li>
             <li>
                 <m>Var(X)=1846.5493749999987</m>
             </li>
             <li>
                 <m>\sigma_X=42.9714949123253</m>
             </li>
         </ol>
          
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
